hishvili\"}, {\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Riner, who jointly lit the cauldron alongside retired sprinter Marie-Jose Perec at last week's Olympics opening ceremony, is the strong favourite to win gold in Paris having stood on the top step of the podium in London and Rio.\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 461, \"end\": 477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"score\": 0.9999999999295142, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marie-Jose Perec\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\"}, {\"begin\": 559, \"end\": 564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4832158329716256e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 611, \"end\": 617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999998160547134, \"rank\": 1.8390648298234737e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 622, \"end\": 625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.10312122833642e-12, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Winning a medal guarantees his spot as the most decorated judoka in Olympic history.But he faced a tricky test on paper in the quarter-finals against Tokyo silver medalist Tushishvili.However, Riner had the home crowd on their feet when he won the match with an ippon - the highest score available in judo.Guram Tushishvili has been disqualified from the Olympics|GETTYThe referee raised his arm to indicate Riner's victory as the Frenchman stood tall over his Georgian opponent.Tushishvili reacted angrily as he pushed his leg upwards into the body of Riner, sending the 35-year-old back down to the canvas.The 29-year-old then kicked the France judoka around on the floor before putting his hand in Riner's face.The pair eventually shook hands after the scuffle, but it was later confirmed by the International Judo Federation that Tushishvili had been disqualified from the Olympics.Their statement read: 'Following the incident that took place at the end of the quarter-final between Teddy Riner (FRA) and Guram Tushishvili (GEO) in the +100 kg weight category, the behaviour of the Georgian judoka was against the 'spirit of judo,' an ad hoc disciplinary commission was called immediately together to investigate the situation.\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 1860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9998782498739667, \"rank\": 0.00012176495078568221, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 821, \"end\": 826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0522865898826704e-14, \"text\": \"Riner\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Riner\"}, {\"begin\": 1036, \"end\": 1041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0522865898826704e-14, \"text\": \"Riner\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"ht